  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Department of Education contract obligations totaled $1.9B in FY2026 to date, with 555 awards and an average award size of $3.4M. Obligations fell 24.5% year over year. Current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Historically, annual obligations ranged from $2.4B to $2.7B across FY21–FY25, with FY21 and FY24 at $2.7B and FY22 and FY23 at $2.4B; FY25 was $2.5B. The FY2026 to date portfolio is concentrated in a small number of large service categories and vendors: the single largest NAICS category is Other Activities Related to Credit Intermediation at $961M, and the three largest vendors are NELNET SERVICING LLC ($294M), MAXIMUS EDUCATION LLC ($250M), and ACCENTURE FEDERAL SERVICES LLC ($237M). The composition and vendor concentration indicate that credit servicing and information technology-related services account for a majority of obligations in the fiscal year to date portfolio.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How did FY2026 obligations compare with prior years?",
        "body": "Obligations in FY2026 to date were $1.9B, down 24.5% year over year. By comparison, recent full fiscal years include FY25 at $2.5B, FY24 at $2.7B, FY23 at $2.4B, FY22 at $2.4B, and FY21 at $2.7B. The FY2026 total is a partial year figure and reflects the fiscal year to date status."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Where is Education concentrating its contract spending in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "Spending is concentrated in credit intermediation and IT-related services: Other Activities Related to Credit Intermediation is $961M and Computer Systems Design Services is $456M. Research and Development in the Social Sciences and Humanities is $142M, and a cluster of other IT and financial processing categories together account for additional obligations. Several large vendors capture substantial shares of obligations, with NELNET SERVICING LLC at $294M and MAXIMUS EDUCATION LLC at $250M."
      }
    ]
  },
  "faq": [
    {
      "q": "How much does Department of Education spend on contracts?",
      "a": "The Department of Education has $1.9B in contract obligations in FY2026 to date. Total award count is 555 with an average award size of $3.4M, and obligations fell 24.5% year over year. Current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date)."
    },
    {
      "q": "What does Education buy?",
      "a": "Education primarily buys credit intermediation and IT and research services. The largest category is Other Activities Related to Credit Intermediation at $961M, followed by Computer Systems Design Services at $456M and Research and Development in the Social Sciences and Humanities at $142M, with additional spending in financial transactions processing, other computer related services, and custom computer programming services."
    },
    {
      "q": "Who are Education's largest contractors?",
      "a": "The largest contractors by obligation in FY2026 to date are NELNET SERVICING LLC ($294M), MAXIMUS EDUCATION LLC ($250M), and ACCENTURE FEDERAL SERVICES LLC ($237M). Other top vendors include EDFINANCIAL SERVICES LLC ($198M), MISSOURI HIGHER EDUCATION LOAN AUTHORITY ($164M), and MAXIMUS FEDERAL SERVICES, INC. ($91.7M)."
    }
